---
import PortalLayout from '../../layouts/PortalLayout.astro'
---

<PortalLayout
  title="Foundation Certificate (Tier 1) — Sohma Institute"
  description="12-week entry point for registered health practitioners. Foundational literacy in one division through online study and clinical intensive."
>
  <article class="tier-page">

    <!-- AT A GLANCE -->
    <header class="tier-header">
      <div class="section-label">Tier 1</div>
      <h1 class="page-title">Foundation Certificate</h1>

      <div class="glance-strip">
        <div class="glance-item">
          <span class="glance-key">Duration</span>
          <span class="glance-val">12 weeks</span>
        </div>
        <div class="glance-divider"></div>
        <div class="glance-item">
          <span class="glance-key">Mode</span>
          <span class="glance-val">Online + Clinical Intensive</span>
        </div>
        <div class="glance-divider"></div>
        <div class="glance-item">
          <span class="glance-key">Credential</span>
          <span class="glance-val">Foundation Certificate</span>
        </div>
        <div class="glance-divider"></div>
        <div class="glance-item">
          <span class="glance-key">Division</span>
          <span class="glance-val">Choose one</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>


    <!-- WHO THIS IS FOR -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Who this is for</h2>
      <p>Registered health practitioners (AHPRA or recognised equivalent) who want to add traditional medicine competencies to their existing scope of practice. This is an entry point, not a standalone qualification. You leave this tier able to understand and engage with the Institute's framework — not yet to practise independently within it.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- WHAT YOU'LL LEARN -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>What you'll learn</h2>
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-card">
          <h3>Systems Biology Primer</h3>
          <p>The foundational scientific framework that underpins the Institute's approach to traditional medicine. Network pharmacology, complex adaptive systems, and the convergence thesis between traditional and modern therapeutic logic.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-card">
          <h3>Clinical Reasoning Methodology</h3>
          <p>Division-specific clinical reasoning frameworks. How to assess, formulate, and plan within your chosen division's therapeutic paradigm. Case-based from the outset.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-card">
          <h3>Regulatory & Ethical Frameworks</h3>
          <p>The regulatory landscape governing traditional medicine practice in Australia. TGA requirements, AHPRA scope considerations, informed consent for complex interventions, and Indigenous knowledge governance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>This tier is framed as <em>literacy</em>. You leave with the ability to understand the Institute's framework, engage with its research and protocols, and make an informed decision about continuing to Tier 2.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- DELIVERY -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Delivery structure</h2>
      <div class="delivery-grid">
        <div class="delivery-block">
          <div class="delivery-tag">Asynchronous</div>
          <h3>Didactic Content</h3>
          <p>Self-paced study modules covering the theoretical and scientific foundations. Completed on your own schedule. This is what you study — not what you attend.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="delivery-block">
          <div class="delivery-tag accent">Synchronous</div>
          <h3>Clinical Intensive</h3>
          <p>The high-value component. Case-based learning sessions, supervised observation within the Sohma House patient population, peer case conferencing. Every synchronous hour is mentorship, not lecture.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ASSESSMENT -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Assessment</h2>
      <p>Portfolio-based. No written examinations. Clinical case documentation begins at this tier — your portfolio becomes the ongoing record of your professional development throughout the Institute's credentialing pathway.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- PREREQUISITES -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
      <p>Current AHPRA registration or recognised international equivalent. No prior training in traditional medicine required — that's what this tier provides.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- PATHWAY FORWARD -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Pathway forward</h2>
      <div class="pathway-cards">
        <div class="pathway-card">
          <div class="pathway-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><polyline points="19 12 12 19 5 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Tier 2 Entry</h3>
          <p>Completion qualifies for direct entry into the Advanced Diploma in your chosen division.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pathway-card">
          <div class="pathway-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Affiliate Network Membership</h3>
          <p>Access to Tier A validated protocols, continuing education, and peer case conferencing through the Practitioner Network.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- FEES -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Fees & funding</h2>
      <p>Tuition fees, payment plan options, and VET Student Loans eligibility details will be published prior to the first intake. Contact the Institute for current information.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="tier-cta">
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a href="#" class="cta-primary">Apply Now</a>
        <a href="#" class="cta-secondary">Enquire</a>
        <a href="/education" class="cta-secondary">Back to all programs</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</PortalLayout>

<style>
  .tier-page {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    padding: 0 clamp(24px, 4vw, 56px);
  }
  .tier-page p { line-height: 1.8; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .tier-page p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .tier-page h1, .tier-page h2, .tier-page h3 { margin: 0; }

  .section-label {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.6875rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em; color: var(--accent-dark); margin-bottom: 1rem; white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .section-label::after { content: ''; flex: 1; height: 1px; background: var(--accent-line); }

  /* ═══ HEADER ═══ */
  .tier-header { padding: 4rem 0 2.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .page-title {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 400; color: var(--text-heading); line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 2rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .glance-strip { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .glance-item { padding: 0 1.5rem; }
  .glance-item:first-child { padding-left: 0; }
  .glance-key { display: block; font-size: 0.5625rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.14em; color: var(--text-tertiary); margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .glance-val { display: block; font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-heading); }
  .glance-divider { width: 1px; height: 36px; background: var(--border-medium); flex-shrink: 0; }

  /* ═══ SECTIONS ═══ */
  .tier-section { padding-bottom: 2.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bg-card); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .tier-section h2 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-heading); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .tier-section p { font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--text-body-70); line-height: 1.8; }

  /* Content cards grid */
  .content-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .content-card {
    background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border-light); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .content-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-heading); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .content-card p { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--text-body-60); line-height: 1.7; }

  /* Delivery grid */
  .delivery-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
  .delivery-block {
    background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border-light); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .delivery-tag {
    display: inline-block; font-size: 0.5625rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--text-tertiary); border: 1px solid var(--border-medium);
    border-radius: 2px; padding: 2px 8px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .delivery-tag.accent { color: var(--accent-dark); border-color: var(--accent-border-20); }
  .delivery-block h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-heading); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .delivery-block p { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--text-body-60); line-height: 1.7; }

  /* Pathway cards */
  .pathway-cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
  .pathway-card {
    background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border-light); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .pathway-icon { color: var(--accent-dark); opacity: 0.6; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .pathway-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-heading); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .pathway-card p { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--text-body-60); line-height: 1.7; }

  /* CTA */
  .tier-cta { padding: 2rem 0 4rem; }
  .cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .cta-primary {
    font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: #fff; background: var(--accent-dark); border-radius: 4px; padding: 12px 28px;
    text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .cta-primary:hover { background: var(--accent-darker-hover); }
  .cta-secondary {
    font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--glass-12); border-radius: 4px; padding: 12px 28px;
    text-decoration: none; transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }
  .cta-secondary:hover { border-color: var(--accent-border-30); color: var(--accent-dark); }

  /* ═══ RESPONSIVE ═══ */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-title { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .glance-strip { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1rem; }
    .glance-divider { width: 60px; height: 1px; }
    .glance-item { padding: 0; }
    .content-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .delivery-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .pathway-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
